  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a continued evaluation of the immune response to StaphVAX , a Staphylococcus
      aureus type 5 and 8 capsular polysaccharide conjugate vaccine, in end-stage renal disease
      patients, by giving a 3rd and 4th dose to a subset of the participants in the previous
      efficacy trial. Participants continue to receive the vaccine or placebo in a blinded manner,
      and are also randomly assigned to 1 of 2 different intervals between the doses. The
      immunogenicity is measured by the antibodies in the blood, and typical vaccine safety
      information is also collected.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
